                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13152154" author="thepaul" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2011 17:35:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a note for future reference- the opinion has been expressed that requiring EPEL for cassandra rpms may not be an option. Might need to remove the 2.5 features from cqlsh and test it along with the python driver on 2.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158621" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 18:46:17 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;for pyver in 2.6 2.7 2.5
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why that particular ordering?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158640" author="thepaul" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 19:03:11 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Why that particular ordering?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No strong reason. 2.6 is just a little more likely to be found than 2.7, over our expected set of install targets, and both 2.6 and 2.7 are little bits faster than 2.5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fine with changing to something else.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158650" author="tjake" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 19:11:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;tested on centos 6 which used 2.4 by default, with this patch it finds the right version so +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158659" author="thepaul" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 19:20:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One minor edit: if we change the shebang from &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#35;&amp;#33;/bin/bash&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#35;&amp;#33;/bin/sh&lt;/tt&gt;, it will work for Solaris too. none of the code actually needs bash.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13161393" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 2 Dec 2011 03:10:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed, with bin/sh&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
